Class GnVideoProduct

java.lang.Object
  com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnObject
      com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnDataObject
          com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnVideoProduct

public class GnVideoProduct
extends GnDataObject

A Product refers to the commercial release of a Film, TV Series, or video content. Products contain a unique commercial code such as a UPC (Univeral Product Code), Hinban, or EAN (European Article Number). Products are for the most part released on a physical format, such as a DVD or Blu-ray.

isFullResult

public boolean isFullResult()
Flag indicating if response result contains full (true) or partial metadata

Remarks:

Available for the following music and video types:
  • Album
  • Contributor
  • Track
  • Product
  • Season
  • Series
  • Work

Note:

What constitutes a full result varies among the individual response types and results, and also depends on data availability.

packageLanguageDisplay

public java.lang.String packageLanguageDisplay()
Package display language, e.g., "English"

Remarks:

The language depends on availability - information in the language set for the locale may not be available, and the object's information may be available only in its default official language. For example, if a locale's set language is Spanish, but the object's information is available only in English, this value returns as English.

packageLanguage

public java.lang.String packageLanguage()
Package language ISO code, e.g., "eng".

Remarks:

GNSDK supports a subset of the ISO 639-2 Language Code List. Specify a locale language's lower-case three-letter code, which is shown in the macro's C/C++ syntax section.

Note:

The following languages use Gracenote-specific three-letter codes:
  • qtb (Simplified Chinese)*
  • qtd (Traditional Chinese)*
